01:55.637 --> 01:57.552
I mean, obviously, it's not the
usual way of doing the pricing,

01:57.552 --> 01:59.902
but I figured if we give people

01:59.902 --> 02:01.773
a high percentage
of the money we make,

02:01.773 --> 02:03.427
they'll be more likely
to give us more things

02:03.427 --> 02:05.647
in the future, so...

02:05.647 --> 02:07.431
In the end, everyone wins.

02:07.431 --> 02:09.781
Have you told Flaxman?

02:09.781 --> 02:13.307
Uh, no. No, I just want
to finish it first.

02:14.308 --> 02:18.964
♪ Christmas presents
around the world ♪

02:18.964 --> 02:23.186
♪ Something mighty sweet
to see ♪

02:23.186 --> 02:26.407
♪ Only if I just had
a present for everyone ♪

02:26.407 --> 02:29.584
♪ Under one great big
Christmas tree ♪

02:31.455 --> 02:35.807
♪ Well, every boy that wants
a brand-new toy ♪

02:35.807 --> 02:39.376
♪ For every Johnny
that wants a car ♪

02:39.376 --> 02:41.204
♪ For every junior...

02:41.204 --> 02:43.685
- Ah, Mr. Flaxman.
- Bernard.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.295
This is Henry Hackford

02:45.295 --> 02:47.602
of the Metropolitan Museum
of Art.

02:47.602 --> 02:48.951
Uh, it's an honor
to meet you, sir.

02:48.951 --> 02:50.518
Nice to meet you, too.

02:50.518 --> 02:52.607
I'd like you to take him
through your new catalog.

02:52.607 --> 02:54.565
The Museum are
potential purchasers

02:54.565 --> 02:56.480
of many of your treasures.

02:56.480 --> 02:57.916
Yes, right.

02:57.916 --> 03:00.354
Um, I'm just kind of late
for something. It's...

03:01.920 --> 03:03.748
Okay. Sure, sure.

03:03.748 --> 03:05.489
Oh, it'd be a pleasure, sir.

03:05.489 --> 03:06.795
Of course. Thank you.

03:06.795 --> 03:09.276
Thank you.

03:09.276 --> 03:11.713
Why are you
carrying such an ugly bear?

03:15.891 --> 03:17.588
It's a particular focus
on cartography

03:17.588 --> 03:19.242
and the natural world.

03:19.242 --> 03:22.506
I'm really proud
of the breadth and...

03:22.506 --> 03:24.682
range of pieces
we've got in this sale.

03:24.682 --> 03:27.424
Thank you.

03:32.560 --> 03:35.911
Work ye, Bernard. Work ye.

04:31.793 --> 04:33.577
Hello, Bernard.

04:33.577 --> 04:35.971
Um, I-I'm so sorry.

04:35.971 --> 04:38.060
I-- Let-let me just
explain everything.

04:38.060 --> 04:40.628
I already know what happened.

04:40.628 --> 04:42.847
It was,
"Of course, Mr. Flaxman,"

04:42.847 --> 04:45.067
and work, work, work.

04:45.067 --> 04:46.982
And you missed
your daughter's birthday.

04:46.982 --> 04:48.418
I mean--

04:48.418 --> 04:50.594
Uh, yes, t-that's
pretty much it.

04:50.594 --> 04:53.118
Really, I'm so sorry, I ju--

04:53.118 --> 04:55.991
Okay. Should I wake her up

04:55.991 --> 04:58.341
so you can give her
your present?

05:00.561 --> 05:02.432
Yeah, uh, yeah.

05:02.432 --> 05:04.347
Yeah, yeah, of course, um...

05:04.347 --> 05:05.827
Uh, just give me one second.

05:05.827 --> 05:08.351
I just, uh, I just need to
sort something.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.364
Oh. Hey.

05:21.364 --> 05:22.974
Hey. Hey, sweetheart.

05:22.974 --> 05:26.456
Happy birthday!

05:26.456 --> 05:27.849
Huh? Okay. Yep.

05:27.849 --> 05:31.896
Um, well, I...
I got this for you.

05:32.897 --> 05:34.508
Groceries?

05:34.508 --> 05:36.640
No, no, uh, let me just
help you with that.

05:40.688 --> 05:43.386
It's a jewelry box,
golden jewelry box.

05:43.386 --> 05:44.866
Unbelievable, Bernie.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.522
I think it's stuck.

05:48.522 --> 05:51.133
Uh, oh, this is
your first antique.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.482
Isn't it pretty?

05:52.482 --> 05:54.136
Sweetie, why don't, um...

05:54.136 --> 05:56.181
you go to your room and pack
a bag for Grandma's, okay?

05:56.181 --> 05:57.705
Okay.

06:01.012 --> 06:04.451
Oh, Bernie.

06:04.451 --> 06:06.888
What are we gonna do? I, um...

06:06.888 --> 06:10.718
I think I'm gonna take Eve
to my mom's like we planned,

06:10.718 --> 06:14.156
but, uh... I'm just gonna
need some time there.

06:14.156 --> 06:17.028
At least through
the holidays and...

06:17.028 --> 06:19.683
I-I think it's best
if you don't come.

06:19.683 --> 06:22.686
What?

06:22.686 --> 06:24.601
Julie, no-- please,
y-you're kidding.

06:24.601 --> 06:25.733
Please be kidding.

06:25.733 --> 06:27.865
No, Bernie, I am so not kidding.

06:27.865 --> 06:30.999
This is the least funny
conversation of my life.

06:30.999 --> 06:33.784
It's been going on
for such a long time.

06:33.784 --> 06:35.046
It's like...

06:35.046 --> 06:37.005
It's like you've
forgotten who we are.

06:37.005 --> 06:38.615
And what a family means. And I--

06:38.615 --> 06:41.139
I'm really sorry about the box.

06:41.139 --> 06:44.621
What she really wanted for
her birthday was a dollhouse.

06:44.621 --> 06:47.668
Though I'm sure an hour of
her dad's undivided attention

06:47.668 --> 06:49.452
would've been just as good.

06:50.497 --> 06:53.500
Bernie, it is one thing
to drop the ball with me,

06:53.500 --> 06:54.849
but with Eve?

07:00.158 --> 07:02.030
I'll be back, okay?

07:03.901 --> 07:05.555
You missed my birthday.

07:05.555 --> 07:08.123
Oh, I'm--
I'm so sorry, sweetheart.

07:08.123 --> 07:11.256
Mom says you're
a selfish bastard.

07:11.256 --> 07:13.824
S-She was joking.

07:15.217 --> 07:16.958
Well, d-darling...

07:16.958 --> 07:20.788
♪ Bells will be ringing

07:20.788 --> 07:23.878
♪ The glad, glad news

07:23.878 --> 07:27.795
♪ Oh, what a Christmas

07:28.796 --> 07:31.886
♪ To have the blues

07:33.627 --> 07:35.890
♪ My baby's gone

07:35.890 --> 07:37.935
- ♪ I have no friends

07:37.935 --> 07:40.111
Come in.

07:40.111 --> 07:42.766
♪ Please come home
for Christmas... ♪

07:42.766 --> 07:46.204
Bernard. Sit ye. Sit ye.

07:46.204 --> 07:48.032
♪ Once again.

07:48.032 --> 07:51.601
Thank you for taking me
through the catalog last night.

07:51.601 --> 07:54.256
It was very eye-opening.

07:54.256 --> 07:55.953
Well, I'm glad
it was for you, sir.

07:55.953 --> 07:57.738
I have to say, it was
a complete disaster for me.

07:57.738 --> 07:59.566
Oh, dear.

07:59.566 --> 08:01.655
By the time
I got home yesterday,

08:01.655 --> 08:03.831
I'd missed
my daughter's birthday.

08:03.831 --> 08:06.050
And then, my wife,

08:06.050 --> 08:09.532
uh, she decided
that she was gonna...

08:09.532 --> 08:13.667
well, sort of move out
for a bit.

08:13.667 --> 08:15.320
That's terrible.

08:15.320 --> 08:19.499
I need to find a way right now
t-to make things right.

08:20.369 --> 08:22.545
What I'm trying to say
is I-I'm gonna need

08:22.545 --> 08:24.895
more than just the holidays off.

08:24.895 --> 08:27.028
I'm gonna need a few more weeks

08:27.028 --> 08:28.638
to fight for my marriage.

08:28.638 --> 08:29.987
Mm.

08:29.987 --> 08:31.554
Yes, of course you are.

08:31.554 --> 08:32.686
Oh.

08:32.686 --> 08:33.991
Really? Oh, thank you, sir.

08:33.991 --> 08:36.167
Will that be enough, though?

08:36.167 --> 08:38.561
I-I honestly don't know, sir.
I hope so.

08:38.561 --> 08:40.824
And what if we take it
one step further?

08:40.824 --> 08:43.000
What if we extend
this sabbatical

08:43.000 --> 08:46.177
to say, I don't know, 12 months?

08:46.177 --> 08:48.963
And after that,
another 12 months.

08:48.963 --> 08:50.878
And then another 12 months.

08:50.878 --> 08:55.012
Are you-- are you suggesting
I take three years off?

08:55.012 --> 08:57.101
Five years. Ten years!

08:57.101 --> 08:58.929
Let's go nuts!

08:58.929 --> 09:01.323
All right. It sort of sounds
like you're firing me, sir.

09:01.323 --> 09:04.195
Yes, I suppose I am.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.677
You're a very evil person, sir.

09:07.677 --> 09:10.811
Or a very clever businessman.

09:10.811 --> 09:13.857
And you'll have years
to decide which.

09:34.661 --> 09:36.097
Bernie.

09:36.097 --> 09:37.359
Hey, Lenny.

09:37.359 --> 09:38.882
What do you think?

09:38.882 --> 09:40.057
They let me spruce
the place up a bit.

09:40.057 --> 09:42.016
Seasonal. Everyone's included.

09:42.016 --> 09:43.974
Yeah, it's very nice.

09:43.974 --> 09:45.976
How you doing, man?

09:46.977 --> 09:48.675
Very badly.

09:48.675 --> 09:50.807
I can tell by looking at you.

09:50.807 --> 09:52.069
It's making me sad.

09:52.069 --> 09:53.984
Okay, well, sorry
to be a downer.

09:53.984 --> 09:55.943
No, no, you want to talk? You
want me to get another chair?

09:55.943 --> 09:58.075
You want to-- I g--
I'm reading this great book.

09:58.075 --> 09:59.381
This might be helpful.

09:59.381 --> 10:01.209
It's a book
about parallel universes.

10:01.209 --> 10:02.863
You know about this?

10:02.863 --> 10:06.736
There might be another you
in another universe,

10:06.736 --> 10:08.738
having a great life right now.

10:08.738 --> 10:11.175
Maybe think about that.
That's uplifting.

10:11.175 --> 10:12.742
Is it not?

10:12.742 --> 10:14.091
Do you-- What are you doing
for Christmas?

10:14.091 --> 10:15.440
You want to come over?

10:15.440 --> 10:17.312
You can hang out with the cats.
It's fun.

10:17.312 --> 10:20.141
You watch them, they fight.
There's one that lives outside.

10:20.141 --> 10:22.317
Y-You're very kind, but...

11:38.393 --> 11:41.135
Oh, my God!

11:41.135 --> 11:43.180
You'd think I'd get used to it,

11:43.180 --> 11:44.747
but I never do.

11:46.183 --> 11:49.056
Okay, no, no, no,
you stay back, just stay back.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.535
I-I don't want to hurt you,

11:50.535 --> 11:52.276
but I will hurt you

11:52.276 --> 11:54.888
if you-- if you don't
get out of here.

11:54.888 --> 11:56.367
No, no, no.

11:56.367 --> 11:58.152
H-Help!

11:58.152 --> 12:00.284
Oh, no. It's fine. What do
you want? What do you want?

12:00.284 --> 12:01.764
Seriously, you can
take everything.

12:01.764 --> 12:03.897
Oh, you're just
wailing and crying

12:03.897 --> 12:05.376
like a little baby goat.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.378
- Uh, I don't know what you're--

12:07.378 --> 12:09.337
I-I don't-- I wish-- I wish
I understood what you're saying.

12:19.782 --> 12:21.349
Is this better?

12:21.349 --> 12:23.960
Is it-- Yeah, I mean, yeah.
Yeah. Yeah.

12:23.960 --> 12:27.572
Okay. Then let's get to it.

12:27.572 --> 12:30.184
Your wish is my command.

12:30.184 --> 12:32.403
Yeah, okay, yeah, no.

12:32.403 --> 12:34.101
That's funny 'cause of the--

12:34.101 --> 12:35.450
I wish you'd stop
trying to kill me.

12:35.450 --> 12:37.800
Oh, this? No, this is--

12:37.800 --> 12:39.802
That's just force of habit.

12:39.802 --> 12:41.891
Who are you?
How'd you get into my house?

12:41.891 --> 12:43.893
Oh, wh--

12:43.893 --> 12:45.852
I was in the box.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.331
O-Okay, sure.

12:47.331 --> 12:49.159
Listen, uh, look,
I-I don't judge you,

12:49.159 --> 12:51.074
or whatever recreational
prescription drug

12:51.074 --> 12:52.989
of choice you've taken.

12:52.989 --> 12:55.818
Just don't touch that. I-I need
you to get out of my house.

12:55.818 --> 12:59.169
Okay? Seriously,
how did you get in?

12:59.169 --> 13:02.390
Okay, I'm going
to talk slower for you.

13:02.390 --> 13:04.479
That box...

13:04.479 --> 13:07.221
that you were rubbing...

13:07.221 --> 13:10.006
I was in it.

13:10.006 --> 13:11.834
Okay, sure.

13:11.834 --> 13:13.270
Sure, and how-- and how do you

13:13.270 --> 13:16.056
get inside a box
that's nine inches wide?

13:16.056 --> 13:18.841
Really good question.
It's a really simple answer.

13:18.841 --> 13:21.409
You know, classic setup.

13:24.629 --> 13:26.153
Angry sorcerer.

13:30.940 --> 13:32.333
You know, crazy eyes.

13:32.333 --> 13:34.204
- Pointed a finger at me.

13:34.204 --> 13:36.467
Puff of smoke. Spinning and
turning trough time and space.

13:39.557 --> 13:41.516
<i>The next thing I know,</i>

13:41.516 --> 13:44.040
I'm inside this stupid box.

13:44.040 --> 13:45.346
Okay, wow, wow.

13:45.346 --> 13:46.869
I know!

13:46.869 --> 13:48.305
Now, that's a strong move.

13:48.305 --> 13:50.264
The "I'm a genie"
home invasion excuse, that's--

13:50.264 --> 13:51.874
It's not an excuse.

13:51.874 --> 13:53.136
I am a genie.

13:53.136 --> 13:54.877
Right, yeah.

13:54.877 --> 13:55.965
- Right, right, right.
- Mm-hmm.

13:55.965 --> 13:56.966
Damn.

13:56.966 --> 13:58.446
I mean, the whole thing is--

13:58.446 --> 14:00.535
No, no, no, you-you...

14:00.535 --> 14:02.972
- Back off.
- Okay. All right.

14:02.972 --> 14:04.408
Let's just...

14:04.408 --> 14:07.977
You make wishes,
and then I make them come true.

14:07.977 --> 14:10.632
That's how
this whole thing works.

14:10.632 --> 14:12.939
Okay, so you're saying
you're an actual genie.

14:12.939 --> 14:15.942
- Correct. We're like ghosts.
- Sure.

14:15.942 --> 14:19.336
Or-or dragons or unicorns.

14:19.336 --> 14:20.685
You know, it's like
you-you think we don't exist,

14:20.685 --> 14:22.383
and then you bump into one
and you're like,

14:22.383 --> 14:24.167
"Oh, hey. Oh, look at that.
A genie, genie, genie.

14:24.167 --> 14:25.212
Genies everywhere."

14:25.212 --> 14:26.517
Okay, well, you better get

14:26.517 --> 14:28.693
your next alibi ready
pretty quick.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.565
Okay, how about this?
Um, I-I wish...

14:30.565 --> 14:31.653
Bring it.

14:31.653 --> 14:33.350
...that my phone wasn't dead.

14:33.350 --> 14:36.005
A-And, oh, I know.
How about a camel?

14:36.005 --> 14:37.398
I wish I had my very own camel.

14:37.398 --> 14:39.008
Huh? That seems
reasonable, right?

14:39.008 --> 14:40.357
Sure thing, boss.

14:40.357 --> 14:43.012
It's whatever floats your boat.

14:45.406 --> 14:47.364
Okay, uh...

14:47.364 --> 14:49.366
I mean, that's
a coincidence. The...

14:49.366 --> 14:50.628
Hmm.

14:50.628 --> 14:52.195
Is that a coincidence?

14:57.461 --> 15:00.116
Okay, I-I-I take back
the camel wish. I take it back.

15:00.116 --> 15:02.379
Everybody always takes
the camel wish back.

15:04.512 --> 15:06.209
Oh, my God.

15:06.209 --> 15:10.039
T-That is
interesting, though. The...

15:15.740 --> 15:18.221
I just don't want Eve
growing up with a dad

15:18.221 --> 15:19.962
who never seems
to put her first.

15:19.962 --> 15:22.051
I had to push back
at some point.

15:22.051 --> 15:24.227
- That's right.

15:24.227 --> 15:26.534
God, the problem
with Bernard is...

15:27.535 --> 15:29.624
And you know I still love him.

15:29.624 --> 15:32.453
But the problem is that
he thinks everything

15:32.453 --> 15:34.150
will just be okay in the end.

15:34.150 --> 15:35.456
Hmm.

15:38.720 --> 15:40.461
He is my guy,

15:40.461 --> 15:42.419
but...

15:42.419 --> 15:44.987
he just won't live
in the real world.

15:47.076 --> 15:48.773
Wow. This is so cool.

15:48.773 --> 15:50.645
Oh, my grandma always
used to say,

15:50.645 --> 15:52.168
"You don't get nothing
for free."

15:52.168 --> 15:53.517
I wish she could see me now.

15:53.517 --> 15:55.302
Hello, Bernard.

15:56.607 --> 16:00.089
Oh, look at you.
You're as thin as a rake.

16:00.089 --> 16:02.178
Okay, on second thought,
no hard feelings, Grandma,

16:02.178 --> 16:03.310
I wish she couldn't.

16:03.310 --> 16:05.094
Got it.

16:05.094 --> 16:07.270
I-I did not like that.

16:07.270 --> 16:09.185
- Okay, so wait, am I...

16:09.185 --> 16:11.666
Have I blown it already?
Am I already out of wishes?

16:11.666 --> 16:14.103
No, keep at it.

16:14.103 --> 16:15.365
What about the whole
three wishes thing?

16:15.365 --> 16:17.280
Fairytale stuff.

16:17.280 --> 16:20.588
Real genies, unlimited wishes.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.111
Wow, we have to be very careful,
don't we?

16:22.111 --> 16:24.548
Uh, you do.
If you want my advice,

16:24.548 --> 16:27.464
I would say
use the words "I wish"

16:27.464 --> 16:30.032
with the caution that you
would usually reserve

16:30.032 --> 16:31.468
for "please castrate me."

16:31.468 --> 16:32.687
Just, you know.

16:35.820 --> 16:38.432
Oh.

16:38.432 --> 16:40.129
What?

16:40.129 --> 16:42.088
- Problem?
- What? N-No, no. Me? No problem.

16:42.088 --> 16:43.611
No, blow away.

16:43.611 --> 16:45.787
I-I just suppose a lot
of things have changed

16:45.787 --> 16:47.223
since you were last out.

16:47.223 --> 16:49.051
- Always do.
- Oh.

16:49.051 --> 16:50.444
It's different
every single time.

16:50.444 --> 16:52.228
Wow, so you've been
out of the box before?

16:52.228 --> 16:54.404
Oh, yeah. I mean, here
and there, yeah. But, I mean...

16:54.404 --> 16:56.493
I don't know,
from the looks of this place,

